BugInstance.ShortMessage: Method names should start with a lower case letter
BugInstance.LongMessage: The method name diamond.cms.server.config.WebConfig.JsonReturnHandler() doesn't start with a lower case letter
diamond.cms.server.dao.JOOQGenericDao.setObjectValue(String, Object, Object, Map) uses String.indexOf(String) instead of String.indexOf(int)

BugPattern.ShortDescription: Method names should start with a lower case letter
BugPattern.Details: Methods should be verbs, in mixed case with the first letter lowercase, with the first letter of each internal word capitalized.

This code passes a constant string of length 1 to String.indexOf(). It is more efficient to use the integer implementations of String.indexOf(). f. e. call myString.indexOf('.') instead of myString.indexOf(".")

BugCode.Description: Inefficient use of String.indexOf(String) or String.lastIndexOf(String)
